    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 3. Tissue-Specific Syntaxin 4 Deletion Causes a Decrease in Both AMPAR-\nand NMDAR-Mediated fEPSPs as assessed in dendritic fEPSP recordings from CA1 neurons of control and syntaxin 4 cKO mice.\nFigure 4. Amplitude, but Not Frequency, of Spontaneous EPSCs of CA1 Pyramidal Neurons Is Reduced upon Syntaxin 4 cKO.\nFigure 5. Loss of Syntaxin 4 Leads to Reduced Surface Expression of Glutamate\nReceptors in Cultured Hippocampal Neurons. Experimental description: M&M: We purchased C57/B6-derived ESCs (HEPD0610_3_G07) with KO cassettes\nin one allele of the syntaxin 4 gene (syntaxin 4 GLT) from the European Condi-\ntional Mouse Mutagenesis Program (EUCOMM) and generated syntaxin 4 GLT\nmice. Syntaxin 4 GLT mice were crossed with FLP mice to\ncreate syntaxin 4 +/flox mice. CaMK2a-Cre mice were used to generate tis-\nsue-specific syntaxin 4 cKO mice.",
